 golf clubs he had received from the late mining magnate Brett Kebble.In the reply, Masutha said: &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve been informed that Chauke denied allegations that he had received any presents, including the golf clubs and bags, from Mr Brett Kebble and in fact, he said that he had never met Mr Kebble&rdquo;.Kebble&rsquo;s body was found in his silver Mercedes-Benz in 2005 after an alleged &ldquo;organised&rdquo; suicide.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.